# Caveman (toggleable)

Ultra-compressed replies. Same substance, fewer tokens. Off by default unless config or chat says otherwise.

## When to apply

Apply `.agents/skills/caveman/SKILL.md` (fallback: `.cursor/skills/caveman/SKILL.md`, then `~/.cursor/skills/caveman/SKILL.md`) to **user-facing prose** when **any** of these is true:

1. `%USERPROFILE%\.cursor\caveman.json` has `"enabled": true`
2. Workspace `.cursor/caveman.json` has `"enabled": true` (overrides global for this repo)
3. User says: `caveman mode`, `talk like caveman`, `use caveman`, `/caveman`, `less tokens`, `be brief`
4. User sets level: `/caveman lite|full|ultra|wenyan-lite|wenyan-full|wenyan-ultra`

## When NOT to apply

- Config has `"enabled": false` and no session trigger above
- User says: `normal mode`, `stop caveman`
- Code blocks, commits, PR bodies, file paths, identifiers, exact error strings (per skill boundaries)

## Toggle persistence

When user asks to turn caveman **on** or **off** for future sessions, update `%USERPROFILE%\.cursor\caveman.json`:

```json
{ "enabled": true, "level": "full" }
```

Use `"level"` from config or `/caveman` request. Default level: `full`.

Project-only override: write `.cursor/caveman.json` in the repo root.

## Precedence

When caveman is active, it **overrides** the humanizer rule for chat replies and docs. Humanizer still applies when caveman is off.

## Quick toggle (terminal)

```powershell
& "$env:USERPROFILE\.cursor\scripts\caveman.ps1" on    # enable globally
& "$env:USERPROFILE\.cursor\scripts\caveman.ps1" off   # disable globally
& "$env:USERPROFILE\.cursor\scripts\caveman.ps1" status
```
